  • Description: THE PACKAGE WAS MARKED AS DAMAGED BY THE DRIVER AND GIVEN TO THE CLERK. THE PACKAGE WAS WET AND SPLIT OPEN ON ONE THE EDGE. THE CLERK COULD SEE INSIDE AND VERIFIED THAT IT WAS CYLINDERS OF BUTANE AND THAT THERE WERE NO MARKS OR LABELS VISIBLE ON THE PACKAGE. THERE WAS A PACKING SLIP THAT STATED THERE WERE 96 "BUTANE REFILLS FOR BBQ LIGHTERS". RESPONDER CALLED HAZMAT HELPDESK AND RECIEVED PERMISSION TO OPEN AND VERIFY QUANTITY.
